    An incredible experience from start to finish.
    I took my partner for his birthday on the legends tour. He's a life long Arsenal fan and he was absolutely blown away with the whole experience. Perry Groves was our guide and his knowledge was second to none. As someone who is not at all in to football I thought I'd be bored but I definitely was not. Perry was funny, and did a really great job of answering questions and his stories were so interesting. I learnt a lot and came away with a bit of a love for the club which is not something I thought I'd ever say. The stadium itself was breathtaking, and the staff were absolute top quality. I have mobility issues and was having a really bad day managing my pain, not wanting to let my partner down I powered on through and although I was struggling alot, staff were on hand to show me towards the lifts which was a real help. We had a wonderful lady called Kelly walking the tour with us. She could clearly see I was struggling, I'm not one to ask for help even when I really need it, but she noticed and next thing I knew she was there with a chair for me to rest on. I've never been so thankful, she is an absolute angel on earth a real credit to you. Not only did my partners dreams come true with this experience, but the kindess and caring nature of Kelly made my time there so much easier. I cannot fault one single thing from the day. It was truly incredible from start to finish, and I can't believe what value for money we got. I'd highly recommend this experience to anyone, I cannot believe what we got for the price we paid. Absolutely incredible!
